  sodium: 1180 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pork-mushroom-carrot-bibimbap-5efb350fa169b168fb03500a
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
time required: 30 minutes
course: main course
cuisine: Asian
---

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups
water (2¼ cups for 4 servings), and a
big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then
cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook
until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep
covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry
all produce. Trim and thinly slice
@Scallions{2}, separating whites from
greens. Trim and peel @Carrots{6%oz}. Using a
#peeler{}, shave carrots lengthwise into
ribbons, rotating as you go. Trim and
thinly slice @Button Mushrooms{4%oz}. Peel and mince
@Ginger{1%thumb} and @Garlic{1%clove}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine scallion
whites, @White Wine Vinegar{5%tsp}, and a pinch of salt.
Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally,
until ready to serve. In a separate small
bowl, combine @Sesame Oil{1%tbsp}, half the @Soy Sauce{2%tbsp} (you'll use the rest later), @Sugar{1%tbsp}, and up to
half the @Sriracha{2%tsp} to taste. Stir until sugar
has dissolved.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP sugar instead of 1 TBSP.

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%tbsp} in a large,
preferably #nonstick pan{}, over medium-high heat. Add carrot ribbons; season
with @salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until
slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove
from pan and set aside. Add mushrooms
and another drizzle of oil to pan. Cook,
stirring, until tender, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season
with salt and pepper. Remove from pan
and set aside with carrots.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same
pan over medium-high heat. Add @Ground Pork{10%oz},
ginger, and garlic. Cook, breaking up
meat into pieces, until pork is browned
and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Add
remaining soy sauce and cook, stirring,
until liquid has mostly evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Season with salt and
pepper. Turn off heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season
with salt and pepper; divide between
#bowls{}. Arrange pork and veggies on top.
Top with pickled scallion whites (and
pickling liquid). Drizzle with sauce and
remaining sriracha to taste. Sprinkle
with scallion greens and serve.